CAIRO Egypt is more than doubling monthly food subsidies, to 50 pounds per person from 21 pounds now, President Abdel Fattah al-Sisi said on Tuesday.Read: Egypt to pump $2.5bn into social welfareEgypt has been hit by soaring inflation since it floated its pound currency in November, leading it to halve in value, and has said it plans to shield its poorest citizens from the effects of austerity measures aimed at reforming its economy.Reuters